  "text": "CdSe MSQD has been reported as a potential phosphor [CITATION_1] . The used MSQD has a significant amount of tail emission all over the visible range and is used to simulate the white emission. By excitation from a UV light, a chromaticity coordinate of (0.324, 0.322) and a high CRI of 93 have been reported from the emission. A potential problem of this approach originates from its emission mechanism. Most part of the spectrum comes from the defect emission which will be hard to repeat for industry processing, and the brightness will be greatly restricted as well.",
